net.dempsy.lifecycle.simple

Class MessageProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dempsy.lifecycle.simple.MessageProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MessageProcessorLifecycle<Mp>

    public class MessageProcessor
extends Object
implements MessageProcessorLifecycle<Mp>

    MessageProcessor is a simple implementation of a MessageProcessorLifecycle where the user can define their specific message processors by implementing the Mp interface. This technique ties the specific implementation of the message processor more tightly to the framework than using the annotation driven approach but may be slightly more efficient.

    To use this class you would instantiate it as the MessageProcessorLifecycle for a Node and give it a Supplier to provide new instances of Mps as the framework demands.

    • Method Detail

      • setEvictable

        public MessageProcessor setEvictable(boolean isEvictable)
        The default setting for isEvictable is false. If your Mp implementation actually implements Mp.shouldBeEvicted() then you should set this to true or Dempsy will never call Mp.shouldBeEvicted().

      • setOutput

        public MessageProcessor setOutput(boolean hasOutputCapability)
        The default setting for hasOutput is false. If your Mp implementation actually implements Mp#ouput() method then you should set this to true or Dempsy will never call Mp#ouput().
